==English==
===Etymology===
From Middle English '''bene''' < Old English '''[[bēan]]''' (bean, pea, legume) < Proto-Germanic '''[[*bauno]]''', of unknown origin.

===Pronunciation===
*bēn, /biːn/, /<tt>bi:n</tt>/
*:'''Homophones''': [[been]]
*:[[Rhymes:English:-iːn|Rhymes: -iːn]]

===Noun===
'''bean''' (''plural'' '''beans''')

#The large edible seed of plants of several genera of ''Fabaceae''.
#The seed [[pod]] of plants of several genera of ''Fabaceae''.

